Adding feeling to this process is crucial for it to impact the subconscious effectively, enhancing the success of your manifestations.
title: How to manifest anything you want? Neuroscientist's 6 steps to manifest right

description: Joe Root, one of England's top cricketers, reached a major milestone by playing his 150th Test match against New Zealand. Despite this achievement, Root was dismissed for a duck, joining an unfortunate club with Steve Waugh and Ricky Ponting. Root's career includes 12,754 runs and 35 centuries, showcasing his consistency in Test cricket.
title: Joe Root joins exclusive club with unwanted record during 150th Test

description: Canada's Competition Bureau sues Google, alleging manipulation of the online advertising market and anti-competitive practices. The lawsuit seeks the divestment of two key advertising technology tools and financial penalties. The case parallels ongoing US antitrust efforts and signals increased global scrutiny of tech giants' market practices.
title: Days after Trump’s tariff announcement, Canada has this ‘problem’ with Google

description: In a joint operation, the Indian Navy and Sri Lankan Navy seized approximately 500kg of crystal methamphetamine from two boats in the Arabian Sea. This operation follows India's Coast Guard's record-breaking seizure of 5.5 tonnes of methamphetamine from a Myanmar fishing boat in the Andaman Sea earlier this week.
title: Indian-Sri Lankan naval joint op busts 500kg crystal meth in Arabian Sea

description: Iskcon clarifies it supports Chinmoy Krishna Das’s rights to peacefully advocate for protecting Hindus, despite his arrest in Bangladesh for sedition. The organization reaffirms support for Hindus' protection and peaceful coexistence, though Das does not officially represent ISKCON Bangladesh.
title: 'Not distancing from supporting rights': Iskcon's clarification on priest's arrest

description: New Zealand's Glenn Phillips made a spectacular one-handed catch during the 1st Test against England at Hagley Oval, Christchurch. Phillips' acrobatic effort at gully broke a strong 151-run partnership between Harry Brook and Ollie Pope. England had earlier bowled out New Zealand for 348 on the first day of the match.
title: WATCH: Glenn Phillips' stunning flying catch against England

description: Australian cricket legends Allan Border and Matthew Hayden were critical of Australia's handling of Virat Kohli during India's dominant win in the first Test in Perth. Border expressed disappointment in Australia's approach, while Hayden pointed out flaws in field placements and tactical decisions, stressing the need for better strategies against India's batting lineup.
title: 'Don't want Kohli full of confidence': Border, Hayden slam Australia's tactics

description: Shubman Gill, recovering from a thumb fracture, was seen practicing in Canberra ahead of the pink-ball Test against Australia. Gill's performance, especially his solid defence, looked promising. Meanwhile, India captain Rohit Sharma is expected to feature in the two-day warm-up game against Prime Minister's XI. The second Test against Australia begins on December 6.
title: Shubman Gill hits the nets in Canberra ahead of second Test

description: Prithvi Shaw, a promising Indian cricketer, remained unsold at the IPL 2025 mega auction in Jeddah. Once regarded as a standout talent, Shaw's inconsistent performance and fitness issues led to his release by Delhi Capitals. DC co-owner Parth Jindal believes Shaw needs to refocus on his fitness and passion for cricket to regain his former stature.
title: 'Once in a while, we all need a jolt': DC co-owner on Prithvi Shaw

description: External affairs minister S Jaishankar compared India's foreign policy evolution with a cricket analogy, highlighting its shift from defensive to proactive against Pakistan. He spoke at the release of Mohinder Amarnath's memoir 'Fearless', praising Amarnath's cricket achievements and drawing parallels with India's pivotal role in international cricket post-1983 World Cup victory.
title: Watch: Jaishankar uses Cricket parallel to decode India’s foreign policy

description: US universities have advised foreign students, including Indians, to return from their winter break before Trump's inauguration on Jan 20 to avoid potential travel bans and scrutiny. Concerns are heightened due to previous experiences with travel restrictions. Universities have adjusted academic calendars, and students are rebooking flights to ensure timely return amidst heightened anxieties.
title: Return before Trump takes office, US universities tell students

description: Royal Challengers Bengaluru reassembled a strong squad at the latest IPL auction in Jeddah, poised under Virat Kohli's potential return as captain after discussing with management. Key acquisitions include Josh Hazlewood for Rs 12.50 crore, with Bhuvneshwar Kumar and Lungi Ngidi bolstering their pace attack. However, the lack of a match-winning spinner remains a concern.
title: 'Kohli will be the captain': ABD opines as ex-RCB star praises squad

description: NASA has captured satellite images of hot lava from Iceland's recent volcanic eruption. The eruption, which began on November 20, has led to lava flows reaching the Blue Lagoon spa and the town of Grindavík, prompting evacuations. Experts warn that such eruptions could continue for decades.
title: Nasa captures satellite image of fiery lava flow close to Iceland’s Blue Lagoon

description: Tesla CEO Elon Musk celebrated Thanksgiving with President-elect Donald Trump at Mar-a-Lago resort, enjoying the festivities including dancing to YMCA along with Trump and his family. Musk also interacted with actor Sylvester Stallone, discussing how the film Demolition Man predicted a 'crazy woke future' 30 years ago.
title: Watch: Elon Musk, Trump celebrate Thanksgiving at Mar-a-Lago, groove to YMCA

description: Railway minister Ashwini Vaishnaw dismissed reports of delays in Vande Bharat sleeper train production due to design issues, clarifying the real cause was the Russian firm's limited experience with larger trains. Vaishnaw assured that the Indian Railways' needs for 16 to 24-coach trains were clearly communicated and production will commence soon.
title: Railway minister refutes delays in Vande Bharat sleeper trains over design

description: Security measures have been increased around the Shahi Jama Masjid in Sambhal, Uttar Pradesh, after tensions escalated due to a violent incident during an ASI examination. The Rapid Action Force has been deployed, and a Judicial Inquiry Commission has been established. The Supreme Court will hear a plea regarding the issue on Friday.
title: Security upped in violence-hit Sambhal ahead of Friday prayers

description: Mahayuti leaders Devendra Fadnavis, Eknath Shinde, and Ajit Pawar meet Union Home Minister Amit Shah to discuss the Maharashtra government formation. Although BJP aims to rehabilitate Fadnavis as CM, they also want Shinde as deputy CM to project unity and minimize reliance on Ajit Pawar.
title: BJP wants Eknath Shinde as Maharashtra deputy CM to project message of unity
Air India revival at midway of a 5-day match: CEO Campbell Wilson

description: Japan’s biggest banks, including Mizuho, Sumitomo Mitsui, and Mitsubishi UFJ, plan to maintain their support for Adani Group despite US bribery charges. In contrast, other global firms like Barclays are reassessing their exposure due to reputational risk concerns. Adani Group denies the allegations, reinforcing its stance with investors.
title: Japanese banks sticking with Adani as Jefferies, Barclays review ties

description: Russia launched extensive missile and drone strikes across Ukraine, targeting power plants and causing widespread blackouts as temperatures dropped. President Putin stated the attacks were a retaliation against Ukraine's use of US-supplied missiles. Ukrainian officials reported significant damage, with calls for increased support from Western allies. US President Biden condemned the attacks as outrageous.
title: Ukraine's 'decision-making centers' in Kyiv could be next, warns Putin

description: President Vladimir Putin warns President-elect Donald Trump to remain cautious after multiple assassination attempts. Putin criticizes the uncivilized US election tactics, highlighting threats against Trump's family and concerns over Western involvement in Ukraine. Putin also cautions against the potential nuclear escalation in Ukraine, showcasing a firm stance on national security.
title: 'He's not safe now, should be cautious': Putin's stark warning for Trump

description: Maharashtra's caretaker chief minister Eknath Shinde states that the Mahayuti alliance will decide on the next chief minister in an upcoming meeting in Mumbai. Shinde confirms no issues with the chief minister’s position and agrees with the Prime Minister's decision. BJP and Shiv Sena leaders emphasize unity and collective decision-making.
title: 'Decision to be taken in Mumbai': Shinde on Maharashtra CM post after key meet

description: Indian consular officials in Canada have been subjected to audio and video surveillance, with their private communications intercepted. India lodged a strong protest with Canada, citing violation of diplomatic provisions. Tensions between India and Canada escalated following diplomat expulsions and accusations related to the killing of a Sikh separatist on Canadian soil.
title: Indian consulate officials in Canada told they're under surveillance: MEA

description: Kerala and Adani Vizhinjam Port Pvt Ltd have signed a supplementary agreement, accelerating revenue sharing from Vizhinjam seaport. With the project now fully operational by 2028 and expanded capacity, the government's revenue share from the port is projected to increase significantly, boosting both state income and tax revenue.
title: Kerala, Adani arm ink supplementary pact on port project

description: Over 140 candidates from the economically weaker section have secured postgraduate medical seats in private colleges despite high tuition fees. Questions have arisen about the authenticity of their EWS certificates. Candidates have reportedly paid up to Rs 1.6 crore, prompting calls for a government investigation to address potential misuse of EWS reservations.
title: ‘EWS’ students get medical seats with course fees of crores

description: British Conservative MP Bob Blackman denounced the persecution of Hindus and the arrest of Iskcon priest Chinmoy Krishna Das in Bangladesh, highlighting the burning of Hindu homes and temples. India's ministry expressed deep concern and urged Bangladesh to ensure the safety of minorities, while Bangladesh's ministry deemed India's statement unfounded.
title: British MP condemns attack on Hindus in Bangladesh, arrest of Chinmoy Das

description: India secured a resounding 295-run victory over Australia in the first Test in Perth, led by captain Jasprit Bumrah. Key contributors included batsmen Yashasvi Jaiswal and Virat Kohli, who both scored centuries, while the bowling unit dismissed Australia for 104 in the first innings. Rohit Sharma will return for the next Test.
title: 'I haven't seen an Asian team...': Wasim Akram lauds Team India

description: US President-elect Donald Trump shared an AI-edited video from 'National Lampoon's Christmas Vacation,' targeting President Joe Biden and Vice President Kamala Harris. The clip, featuring swapped faces with notable Democrats and a surprising Trump cameo, generated mixed reactions from social media users. Trump also criticized the 'radical left' and expressed optimism about America's future on his Truth Social platform.
title: Watch: Trump shares AI-generated Thanksgiving video mocking Biden, Kamala

description: Sunil Gavaskar predicts two changes for India's second Test against Australia, with Rohit Sharma and Shubman Gill returning. Captain Sharma will replace Devdutt Padikkal, and Gill may bat at three. Jadeja might replace Washington Sundar in spin bowling. The upcoming warm-up match in Canberra is crucial for India's preparations for the day-night Test in Adelaide.
title: 'KL Rahul will bat at...': Sunil Gavaskar on India XI for Adelaide Test

description: Patrick Collison's social media post showing Tel Aviv's beachfront sparked an intense debate amid recent violence in Gaza. Notable figures like Paul Biggar and Josh Kushner engaged in the discussion, addressing issues of Israeli policies, anti-Semitism, and calls for a boycott of Stripe.
title: In a post, billionaire defends tech CEO for visiting Israel: ‘Saddened ...'

description: Pankaj Rajbhar, 24, was killed by a car driven by Chhotu and Rohit Singh in Jaunpur due to longstanding family rivalry. The horrific incident happened publicly at Makar crossing, sparking protests. Police have filed an FIR and are searching for the accused. Pankaj's family demands immediate arrests, leading to a tense standoff resolved by officials.
title: Old rivalry turns gory: Two repeatedly crush man under car in UP
Rs 100 crore assets in Nagaland crypto scam linked to Chinese seized
Need stricter laws to curb vulgarity on social media: I&B minister Ashwini Vaishnaw

description: The question of banning social media use among children in India gains attention after Australia's new law. Experts believe the ban is well-intentioned but challenging to enforce, advocating for healthy use instead. APA advises that excessive social media can impair adolescents' roles and cause psychological harm.
title: Social media ban for kids not feasible, but need to promote healthy use, say experts

description: BJP's Devendra Fadnavis thanked Union home minister Amit Shah for his support during the Maharashtra Assembly elections. Fadnavis credited Shah for motivating party workers. A positive meeting in New Delhi between BJP and Mahayuti leaders was held, with discussions on finalizing the chief minister's post after BJP secured the most seats in the elections.
title: Fadnavis thanks Amit Shah for support in Maharashtra elections

description: West Bengal CM Mamata Banerjee condemns any violence linked to religion and expresses her sorrow over attacks on minorities in Bangladesh. She urges the Centre to resolve the issue through dialogue with Bangladesh and supports coexistence and harmony among various religions. Banerjee criticizes the Centre's approach and lack of consultation with her government on related matters.
title: Will back Centre on Bangladesh, says Mamata Banerjee
Bangladesh HC junks Iskcon ban plea, asks govt to be vigilant
